        <num>Chapter 59-10</num>
        <heading>Individual Income Tax Act</heading>
        <section eId="sec_59_10_502">
          <num>59-10-502</num>
          <heading>Persons required to file returns.</heading>
          <content>
            <p>59-10-502.
Persons required to file returns.
An income tax return with respect to the tax imposed by this chapter shall be filed by:
(1)
every resident individual, estate, or trust required to file a federal income tax return for the taxable year; and
(2)
every nonresident individual, estate, or trust having federal gross income derived from sources within the state for the taxable year and required to file a federal income tax return for such taxable year.
Renumbered and Amended by Chapter
2
, 1987 General Session</p>
          </content>
          <subsection eId="59_10_502__subsec_1">
            <num>(1)</num>
            <content>
              <p>every resident individual, estate, or trust required to file a federal income tax return for the taxable year; and</p>
            </content>
          </subsection>
          <subsection eId="59_10_502__subsec_2">
            <num>(2)</num>
            <content>
              <p>every nonresident individual, estate, or trust having federal gross income derived from sources within the state for the taxable year and required to file a federal income tax return for such taxable year.</p>
            </content>
          </subsection>
        </section>
